  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1602840599" />
    <a title="Jeanne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/40302787-jeanne"><img alt="Jeanne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1457659064p2/40302787.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1602840599?book_show_action=true">Apr 06, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeanne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeanne" href="/user/show/40302787-jeanne">Jeanne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/17724765-the-friend-from-mexico">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1602840599" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15055224861603746580"><strong>Paraglider</strong><br/><br/>Very well written. The story of a champion stunt paraglider who nearly died in a paragliding accident and his progression back to health. Injured at the Mexican paragliding competition. Apostolos is taken to a Mexican hospital were he spends a month with various complications before being Air Evac&apos;d home to Greece. He narrates his fears and joys of his recovery. At the happy ending, 3 years later, Apostolos is the first person with disabilities (paraplegic) to get a pilots licence with</span>
  <span id="freeText15055224861603746580" style="display:none"><strong>Paraglider</strong><br /><br />Very well written. The story of a champion stunt paraglider who nearly died in a paragliding accident and his progression back to health. Injured at the Mexican paragliding competition. Apostolos is taken to a Mexican hospital were he spends a month with various complications before being Air Evac'd home to Greece. He narrates his fears and joys of his recovery. At the happy ending, 3 years later, Apostolos is the first person with disabilities (paraplegic) to get a pilots licence with a specially modified hands-only airplane so he could do stunt flying.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15055224861603746580" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


